Program: Outlook
Title: 20/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00k404d
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 21 Sep 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, a woman in Somalia who runs the first advice hotline in the capital Mogadishu for women who've been raped and abused. Find out why Fartun Abdisalaam returned to work in the country where her husband had been murdered. An extraordinary family reunion in Cambodia between Phyrun Peou and the father he was sure had been killed in the Khmer Rouge's killing fields in the 1970s. And we meet Lesego Malatsi, the South African designer who's made the switch from Soweto to style guru and is showing a collection at London Fashion Week. Show less